<p>The preparation of Zimpua (ritual incense) is one of the traditional arts of Tibet. This incense is composed of 35 different spices and aromatic substances. The excellence of Zimpua is not merely in the purity of the ingredients, but in the manner of its formulation as well. It is prepared with great care and in accordance with the traditions preserved through the centuries within the monastic orders of Tibet. Tasi Tagge incense is handmade in the monastries of Nepal and each box contains 100 gram if incense working out to approx 44 sticks per box and the sticks are a large 30cm long (approx) making this great value incense.</p>